\title{Jon Sterling}
\author{jonmsterling}
\meta{author}{false}

\p{I am an \em{Associate Professor in Logical Foundations and Formal Methods} at the [University of Cambridge](https://www.cst.cam.ac.uk/people/js2878/), and a Bye-Fellow of [[jms-00GP]] (elected to Fellowship commencing October 2024). I study programming languages and semantics using type theory, category theory, domain theory, and topos theory as a guide. My other interests include Near Eastern, Classical, and Germanic philology. Find my contact information [here](https://www.cst.cam.ac.uk/people/js2878). See [my bibliography](jms-0064) and my [list of students](jms-0063).}

